<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-109-051 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 951 134</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  July 8 1991 v13 n27 p30(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Visual Basic: not the ultimate programming environment. (MicrosoftVisual Basic)(Tech Talk) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gibson, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft Corp's Visual Basic is one of the best development toolsavailable for the Windows operating environment, but is not apanacea for programming problems.andP;  Visual Basic leverages theunderlying power of Windows and is extremely easy to use, butsuffers from the inherent weaknesses of the BASIC programminglanguage.andP;  BASIC uses 'implicit' variable declarations, underwhich variables are created on the fly during program execution; amisspelled variable name can cause a serious bug in a program.andP;  Italso lacks the semantic power and flexibility of the C language.andO;Visual Basic cannot create dialog boxes on the fly.andP;  Thesedifficulties will prevent Visual Basic from appealing to seriousdevelopers, but the tool is nevertheless very useful for creatinginteractive applications.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Products).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   Visual Basic (Program development software) (Design andconstruction).andO;Topic:     Program development softwareBASICProgramming.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>